name: Joel Embiid
summary: Joel Embiid, the Philadelphia 76ers superstar, has been the subject of various news articles due to his recent playoff performance and health concerns. Despite making NBA playoffs history with a 50-point eruption, Embiid has faced criticism for "dirty" play. Amidst speculation of a possible injury, it has been revealed that Embiid is battling Bell's palsy, which caused rumors fueled by his post-game interview. Despite his condition, Embiid dropped an NBA playoff career-high 50 points, leading the 76ers to victory over the Knicks. There have been discussions about the possibility of shutting Embiid down, but the Sixers have no plans to do so. After a recent dunk in the playoffs, Embiid experienced pain, raising concerns about his knee. However, reports indicate that his fate rests on the shoulders and knee of the star player. Embiid has also discussed receiving treatment for Bell's palsy during the playoffs, demonstrating his determination to overcome challenges.

summary: Recent headlines highlight various controversies and developments surrounding Woolworths. Allegations have emerged that Woolworths, Coles, and Aldi employ misleading promotional labels. A pay bungle has earned Woolworths the dubious title of "model accused," costing the company $1 million. To combat retail crime, Woolworths NZ has implemented body cameras. The supermarket has been fined $1.2 million for underpaying workers' long service leave in Victoria. A change in the deli department has sparked outrage, and an Anzac-themed gaffe on a Woolworths mudcake has drawn attention. Additionally, Woolworths has rejected proposals for forced store divestment and reaffirmed its opposition to such measures.
